# Zer0pa Genesis-DM3 Research and Receipt License v1.0

**SPDX Identifier:** `LicenseRef-Zer0pa-GDM3-RRL-1.0`
**Master Resolver Endpoint:** `https://github.com/Zer0pa/ZPE-License-Commercial` (initial; relocatable under §19)
**License Date:** published at the Master Resolver Endpoint for this version.
**Licensor:** Zer0pa (legal name and domicile as published at the Master Resolver Endpoint).

---

## Preamble

This License governs use of two related deterministic geometric artefacts published by the Licensor as part of its Computation work: **DM3** (three-dimensional Double Meru, a 380-vertex C3-symmetric graph artefact) and **Genesis** (a 285-vertex D6-symmetric comparative-determinism artefact constructed on a P₉₅ □ K₃ substrate). Each artefact is distributed as a deterministic binary together with its associated receipt chain, claims documentation, and retractions, collectively described in Section 3 as the **Covered Artefacts**.

The two Covered Artefacts are siblings: they share a deterministic-construction posture, a receipts-first scientific discipline, and a single Licensor, but they are not parts of one underlying technology and no claim of a unified architecture or generalised cross-artefact computation is made by this License. They are licensed together because they evolve together; if a third related artefact is later added to this License, this License will be revised or superseded.

Both Covered Artefacts are distributed in a scientific posture the Licensor calls **receipts-first**: claims are pre-registered with kill-criteria; failed claims are retracted on the public record as first-class outputs; the receipt chain and canonical SHA bundle anchor every public statement to a reproducible artefact. The License is designed to preserve that posture across all downstream use, for both Covered Artefacts.

The Licensor makes no claim, either in this License or in the works it governs, that any Covered Artefact constitutes, embodies, or produces artificial intelligence, artificial general intelligence, cognition, consciousness, awareness, or any mystical, esoteric, or supernatural phenomenon. Each Covered Artefact is a geometric and computational artefact. The DM3 construction draws on the topology of the Sri Yantra, a classical figure of Indian origin and shared cultural heritage; the Licensor's contribution to DM3 is the three-dimensional lattice, the deterministic construction code, and the receipt chain, not the underlying classical figure. The Genesis construction is an independent comparative-determinism artefact on a P₉₅ □ K₃ substrate; it does not draw on Sri Yantra topology and carries no equivalent traditional-knowledge provenance.

Commercial use above the Revenue Threshold, hosting or managed-service provision of any Covered Artefact to third parties, and any use that modifies a Covered Artefact's identity or representations of its scientific status are outside the scope of this License and require a separate Commercial License.

By exercising any right granted here in respect of any Covered Artefact, You accept this License as to that Covered Artefact and as to any other Covered Artefact You subsequently use.

