## 1. Definitions

For the purposes of this License:

**"Artefact Bundle"** means, in respect of a particular Covered Artefact, the complete set of files constituting that Covered Artefact as published by the Licensor at the Master Resolver Endpoint, including without limitation: the deterministic Binary for that Covered Artefact, its adjacency data, its tag or annotation data, its receipt files, its claims documentation, its is/is-not documentation, and its geometry construction and findings documentation. References to "the Artefact Bundle" without further qualification apply distributively across each Covered Artefact.

**"Canonical Bundle Hashes"** means the SHA-256 hashes of each file in the Artefact Bundle of a Covered Artefact, as published in the Artefact Bundle Register at the Master Resolver Endpoint for that Covered Artefact.

**"Change Date"** has the meaning given in Section 10.

**"Claims Document"** means, in respect of a particular Covered Artefact, the file or URL published at the Master Resolver Endpoint (initially `CLAIMS.md`) listing that Covered Artefact's current active claims.

**"Commercial License"** means a separate written agreement between the Licensor and a user, obtained per Section 14, for uses outside the scope of this License.

**"Covered Artefacts"** means **DM3** and **Genesis** as identified in Section 3. References in this License to "DM3," "Genesis," or "the Licensed Work" apply to each Covered Artefact independently and to all Covered Artefacts jointly where the context so admits.

**"DM3"** means the three-dimensional Double Meru artefact identified in Section 3.1, including its Binary, adjacency data, tag data, Receipt Chain, Claims Document, Is/Is-Not Document, and construction and findings documentation.

**"DM3 Binary"** means the Licensor-compiled executable for DM3 identified in the Artefact Bundle Register and verifiable by its Canonical Bundle Hash (as at the License Date, a binary of approximately 9.5 megabytes with SHA-256 as published at the Endpoint).

**"Genesis"** means the 285-vertex D6-symmetric comparative-determinism artefact identified in Section 3.2, including its Binary (or deterministic Rust pipeline), its substrate adjacency data, its receipt chain, its claims documentation, its is/is-not documentation, and its construction and findings documentation.

**"Genesis Binary"** means, in respect of Genesis, the Licensor-published deterministic build (binary, Rust crate output, or platform-specific artefact) identified in the Artefact Bundle Register for Genesis and verifiable by its Canonical Bundle Hashes.

**"Hosted Service"** means any arrangement under which a third party (other than You) can exercise functionality of any Covered Artefact — including without limitation queries, computations, receipt generation, verification, or any interaction that produces outputs — through a network-accessible interface, regardless of whether the third party receives the relevant Binary, adjacency data, receipts, or any other component of the Artefact Bundle.

**"Is/Is-Not Document"** means, in respect of a particular Covered Artefact, the file or URL published at the Master Resolver Endpoint (initially `IS_AND_IS_NOT.md`) stating what that Covered Artefact is and is not.

**"Kill Criterion"** means a pre-registered, publicly recorded, falsifiable condition the failure of which causes the associated Claim to be moved to the Retractions Register for the Covered Artefact to which it relates.

**"License"** means this Zer0pa Genesis-DM3 Research and Receipt License v1.0, together with the Canonical References defined in Section 19.

**"Licensed Work"** means each Artefact Bundle (i.e. the DM3 Artefact Bundle and the Genesis Artefact Bundle), individually and together.

**"Licensor"** means Zer0pa, under the legal name and domicile published at the Master Resolver Endpoint.

**"Master Resolver Endpoint"** has the meaning given in Section 19.

**"Operational Documentation"** has the meaning given in Section 18.

**"Receipt Chain"** means, in respect of a particular Covered Artefact, the ordered set of receipt files published by the Licensor at the Master Resolver Endpoint for that Covered Artefact, anchored to its Binary and Canonical Bundle Hashes, and any successor receipt files subsequently published by the Licensor for that Covered Artefact.

**"Retractions Register"** means the file or URL published at the Master Resolver Endpoint recording Claims that have been retracted and the reason for retraction, including any prior published claim so recorded.

**"Revenue Threshold"** means one hundred million United States dollars (USD 100,000,000) in aggregate gross revenue of an Entity and its Affiliates in the trailing twelve-month period, measured on the date on which commercial use within the meaning of Section 5 is first made and on each subsequent anniversary.

**"Scientific Framing Restriction"** has the meaning given in Section 6.5.

**"Sri Yantra"** means the classical geometric figure of Indian origin from which the topology of DM3 is derived.

**"Substantial Derivative"** means any work that (i) reuses, incorporates, or is otherwise derived from the Binary of any Covered Artefact, its adjacency data, its tag data, or any Receipt for that Covered Artefact, **and** (ii) reproduces, presents, or purports to reproduce that Covered Artefact's outputs in a manner that would lead a reasonable reader familiar with the Covered Artefact to treat the work as representing that Covered Artefact's results. In applying clause (ii), a tribunal may have regard to the work's title, the presentation of receipts or Canonical Bundle Hashes, the prominence of any reference to the Covered Artefact (whether by name, by SHA, or otherwise), and the clarity of any disclaimer distinguishing the work's outputs from the Covered Artefact's outputs. A work that (x) clearly distinguishes its own outputs from the Covered Artefact's outputs, (y) cites the Covered Artefact only as a reference, and (z) does not reproduce or represent that Covered Artefact's Receipts or Canonical Bundle Hashes as its own, is not a Substantial Derivative.

**"You"** means an individual or Entity exercising rights under this License. "Entity" means any legal person. "Affiliates" means Entities under common Control. "Control" means ownership of more than fifty percent (50%) of the voting securities or equivalent beneficial interest, or the power to direct management, of an Entity.

