## 3. Licensed Work — Covered Artefacts

The Licensed Work consists of the Artefact Bundles of each Covered Artefact. The composition of each Artefact Bundle, the Canonical Bundle Hashes, and the identity of each constituent file are published at the Master Resolver Endpoint. As at the License Date, the Covered Artefacts are:

### 3.1 DM3 — Three-Dimensional Double Meru

The DM3 Artefact Bundle, comprising:

(a) the **DM3 Binary** — the deterministic executable implementing the DM3 construction, as compiled and distributed by the Licensor;

(b) the **DM3 adjacency data** — the edge list or equivalent serialisation of the DM3 geometry, constructed as a three-dimensional Double Meru and comprising a C3-symmetric graph of 380 vertices as described in the construction documentation;

(c) the **DM3 tag data** — the vertex and edge tag annotations supporting the construction;

(d) the **DM3 Receipt Chain** — the receipt files produced by the DM3 Binary and published by the Licensor, anchored to the Canonical Bundle Hashes and the six-gate self-certification described in the construction documentation;

(e) the **DM3 Claims Document** and the **DM3 Is/Is-Not Document**;

(f) the **DM3 construction and findings documentation** — the textual description of how the DM3 geometry is constructed and the scientific status of each published claim.

For the avoidance of doubt as to DM3:

1. The Licensor distributes the DM3 Binary as a compiled executable. The source for the supporting internal crate `dm3_microtx` is not part of the DM3 Artefact Bundle and is not distributed under this License. Any redistribution of the DM3 Binary under Section 4 must preserve its Canonical Bundle Hash; no licence is granted to reverse-engineer, disassemble, or otherwise derive the source of `dm3_microtx` except as permitted by mandatory applicable law.

2. The state space referenced in the DM3 construction documentation (approximately 72,960 dimensions) is a property of the artefact, not a claim about general-purpose computation or cognition. It is recorded here for artefact-identification purposes only.

### 3.2 Genesis — 285-Vertex D6-Symmetric Comparative-Determinism Artefact

The Genesis Artefact Bundle, comprising:

(a) the **Genesis Binary** — the Licensor-published deterministic build (binary, Rust crate output, or platform-specific deterministic artefact) implementing the Genesis construction;

(b) the **Genesis substrate adjacency data** — the edge list or equivalent serialisation of the Genesis geometry, constructed on a P₉₅ □ K₃ Cartesian-product substrate and comprising a D6-symmetric graph of 285 vertices as described in the construction documentation;

(c) the **Genesis tag data** — the vertex and edge tag annotations supporting the construction (where applicable to this artefact);

(d) the **Genesis Receipt Chain** — the receipt files produced by the Genesis Binary and published by the Licensor, anchored to the Genesis Canonical Bundle Hashes (as at the License Date, including the cross-platform set of 1,560 byte-identical SHA-256 hashes recorded on commodity Android hardware as described in the Genesis construction documentation);

(e) the **Genesis Claims Document** and the **Genesis Is/Is-Not Document**;

(f) the **Genesis construction and findings documentation** — the textual description of how the Genesis geometry is constructed, the determinism methodology (pure-rational arithmetic), and the scientific status of each published claim.

For the avoidance of doubt as to Genesis:

1. The Licensor distributes the Genesis Binary in the form identified at the Master Resolver Endpoint for Genesis. Where any internal crate or sub-component of the Genesis pipeline is not part of the Genesis Artefact Bundle, it is not distributed under this License; the corresponding restriction in Section 4 applies (preservation of Canonical Bundle Hash; no licence to reverse-engineer or derive the source of internal crates excluded from the Bundle, except as permitted by mandatory applicable law).

2. The Genesis vertex count (285) and substrate identification (P₉₅ □ K₃) are properties of the artefact, not claims about general-purpose computation or cognition.

### 3.3 Authoritative Composition

The Master Resolver Endpoint publishes, and updates from time to time under Section 19, the authoritative composition of each Covered Artefact's Artefact Bundle and its Canonical Bundle Hashes. Where there is any inconsistency between this Section and the current publication at the Master Resolver Endpoint, the current publication controls for purposes of identifying the Licensed Work, subject to Section 19.7 (substantive terms unchanged).

### 3.4 Independence of Covered Artefacts

The Covered Artefacts are independent. A Receipt produced by one Covered Artefact's Binary is a Receipt of that Covered Artefact only, and may not be represented as a Receipt of the other. A Canonical Bundle Hash applies to one Covered Artefact's files only. The two Covered Artefacts are licensed under the same License because they evolve together, not because they share a single underlying construction; nothing in this License creates or implies a unified architecture.

