## 5. Revenue Threshold and Commercial Use

**5.1 Revenue-Gated Commercial Use.** You may make commercial use of the Licensed Work without a Commercial License only if, at the time of such commercial use and on each subsequent anniversary, Your aggregate gross revenue and that of Your Affiliates in the trailing twelve-month period does not exceed the Revenue Threshold. For clarity: all use within the scope of the Section 4 grant is permitted up to and until the Revenue Threshold is crossed.

**5.2 Above the Revenue Threshold.** If Your aggregate revenue exceeds the Revenue Threshold, further commercial use (as distinct from internal research, citation, or academic use, which remain within the Section 4 grant) requires a Commercial License obtained under Section 14.

**5.3 Hosted Service.** Irrespective of the Revenue Threshold, operating a Hosted Service that exposes DM3 functionality to third parties requires a Commercial License.

**5.4 Revenue Measurement.** The Revenue Threshold is measured in United States dollars at the prevailing spot rate on the measurement date. Aggregation across Affiliates is required. You are responsible for accurate good-faith self-measurement. In connection with a bona fide dispute under Section 17, the Licensor may require You, upon not less than thirty (30) days' written notice, to provide a written certification signed by a responsible officer of Your Entity confirming compliance with the Revenue Threshold for the relevant period, together with reasonable supporting evidence. Such evidence will be treated as confidential information and used only for the purpose of resolving the dispute.

**5.5 Industry-Specific Licensing.** The Licensor reserves the right to require a Commercial License for use in specific industries or applications where the Licensor has published industry-specific terms at the Master Resolver Endpoint, irrespective of the Revenue Threshold. Any industry-specific terms so introduced take effect prospectively only, no earlier than thirty (30) days after conspicuous publication at the Master Resolver Endpoint, and do not retroactively affect commercial use lawfully undertaken before their effective date. As of the License Date, no such industry-specific terms are in force.

