## 6. Restrictions

Notwithstanding any grant in Section 4, You may not, without a Commercial License obtained under Section 14 or other written authorisation from the Licensor:

**6.1 No Hosted or Managed Service.** Operate any Hosted Service that exposes the functionality of any Covered Artefact to third parties. Internal-only deployment that serves solely You or Your Affiliates, and that is not made available to third parties under any commercial, evaluative, or operational arrangement, is not a Hosted Service.

**6.2 Anti-Circumvention.** Take any action whose purpose or effect is to circumvent the Revenue Threshold, the Hosted Service restriction, or any other restriction of this License. Circumvention includes without limitation: fragmenting activity across Affiliates or counterparties to keep individual entities below the Revenue Threshold where the aggregate exceeds it; restructuring a Hosted Service as a nominally-internal deployment that in substance exposes any Covered Artefact's functionality to third parties; relabelling outputs of any Covered Artefact as outputs of a third system for the purpose of evading this License. The substance of Your conduct controls over its form.

**6.3 Binary-Only Redistribution Constraint.** You may redistribute the Binary of a Covered Artefact only as published by the Licensor, preserving its Canonical Bundle Hash. You may not:

(a) redistribute any compiled variant of a Covered Artefact's Binary produced from other source;

(b) publish or redistribute the source of any internal crate excluded from a Covered Artefact's Artefact Bundle (including, in respect of DM3, `dm3_microtx`), or any derivative of it whether or not independently obtained, except as may be permitted by mandatory applicable law and only to the extent so permitted;

(c) represent any other compiled binary, whether Yours or a third party's, as DM3, as Genesis, or as any other Covered Artefact.

**6.4 No Fabricated or Modified Receipts.** You may not (a) fabricate Receipts and represent them as elements of the Receipt Chain of any Covered Artefact; (b) modify any Receipt and represent the modified form as authentic; (c) publish receipts produced by a modified copy of a Covered Artefact's Binary as Receipts of that Covered Artefact; (d) selectively publish portions of the Receipt Chain of any Covered Artefact in a manner that materially misrepresents the status of a Claim; (e) cross-attribute Receipts between Covered Artefacts (a DM3 Receipt is not a Genesis Receipt and vice versa).

**6.5 Scientific Framing Restriction.** You may not publicly represent, or allow to be represented on Your behalf, any Covered Artefact or any Substantial Derivative as:

(a) an artificial intelligence, artificial general intelligence, cognitive system, reasoning system, conscious system, or a system that possesses, embodies, or produces any of the foregoing;

(b) a system having mystical, esoteric, spiritual, religious, supernatural, or metaphysical properties;

(c) a system that does anything other than what the Claims Document, as at the relevant time, states it does; or

(d) a system whose retracted claims are active, without fair and legible reference to the Retractions Register.

Nothing in this Section 6.5 restricts good-faith research critique, reproduction efforts, or falsification attempts, including discussion of framings the Licensor has non-claimed for the purpose of evaluating or dismissing them. The target of this Section 6.5 is the marketing, promotional, commercial, or popular-press re-framing of any Covered Artefact in terms the Licensor has expressly non-claimed; it is not the discussion of such framings in bona fide scientific or scholarly criticism.

**6.6 No Identity Spoofing.** You may not represent any work not authored by the Licensor as being DM3, as being Genesis, as being any other Covered Artefact, or as being endorsed by the Licensor. The Artefact Bundle Register at the Master Resolver Endpoint is dispositive for authorship and canonicity.

**6.7 No License Replacement.** You may not distribute the Licensed Work or any Substantial Derivative under a different license purporting to supersede this License, except after the Change Date and under the narrow post-Change-Date terms of Section 10.

