## 7. Receipt Chain Integrity and Retraction Protection

**7.1 Receipt Chain Integrity.** The Receipt Chain of each Covered Artefact is a material term of this License. You acknowledge that the scientific status of each Covered Artefact and of any claim made about it depends on the integrity of its Receipt Chain and its Canonical Bundle Hashes. You will:

(a) preserve the Canonical Bundle Hashes and the integrity of the Receipt Chain when redistributing the Artefact Bundle of any Covered Artefact;

(b) cite the specific Receipt of the relevant Covered Artefact when making a factual claim about that Covered Artefact's outputs;

(c) not represent a Receipt as having been generated from a Covered Artefact's Binary unless the Canonical Bundle Hash of the binary used is the then-current Canonical Bundle Hash published at the Master Resolver Endpoint for that Covered Artefact, or a prior Canonical Bundle Hash so published and retained in the Endpoint's history;

(d) not cross-attribute Receipts between Covered Artefacts.

**7.2 Retraction Protection.** The Retractions Register of each Covered Artefact is a material term of this License. Retractions published at the Master Resolver Endpoint (including, as at the License Date, the DM3 H2 kill and the DM3 γ retraction) are binding on all licensees prospectively from their publication, as to the Covered Artefact whose Register records the retraction. You will:

(a) not represent a retracted Claim as active;

(b) where You have previously published material relying on a retracted Claim, take commercially reasonable steps to make the retraction visible to readers of that material, including by (i) updating any preprint, working paper, institutional repository copy, project website, or other version of the material over which You have control; (ii) posting an erratum or correction note on Your own controlled channels (such as a laboratory, project, or institutional website); and (iii) where the publication venue permits, submitting a formal erratum or addendum to that venue. This obligation is to act in good faith to surface the retraction; it does not require amendment of immutable external publications outside Your control;

(c) accept that future retractions, pre-registered kill criterion outcomes, or changes to the Claims Document published at the Master Resolver Endpoint take effect prospectively from publication, without amendment of this License.

**7.3 Evidence of Integrity.** The Licensor may request, as part of any dispute under Section 17, reasonable evidence of Your compliance with this Section 7. Wilful fabrication, modification, or misrepresentation of Receipts, Canonical Bundle Hashes, or retraction status is a material breach, not curable under Section 16.2.

