## 8. Traditional Knowledge Acknowledgment (DM3 only)

**8.0 Scope.** This Section 8 applies to DM3 only. Genesis is an independent comparative-determinism artefact constructed on a P₉₅ □ K₃ substrate; it does not draw on Sri Yantra topology and is not subject to this Section.

**8.1 Acknowledgment.** The topology on which the DM3 geometry is based is the Sri Yantra, a classical geometric figure of Indian origin and shared cultural heritage. The Licensor claims no proprietary right, and asserts no cultural authority, over the Sri Yantra itself. The Licensor's work in DM3 is the three-dimensional lattice construction ("3D Double Meru"), the deterministic construction code, and the receipt chain and tests that accompany it.

**8.2 Required Acknowledgment.** When citing DM3 in a context that references its geometric construction, You will reference the Sri Yantra as the classical topological source and the Licensor's work as the lattice construction. A reasonable form of acknowledgment is sufficient; elaborate or ritualised form is not required. The acknowledgment may be integrated into Your citation of DM3 or may appear separately, at Your discretion.

**8.3 Non-Appropriation.** You may not claim proprietary ownership of the Sri Yantra figure itself or of any traditional knowledge on which it draws, in Your own name or on behalf of the Licensor.

