## 19. Canonical References and Master Resolver Endpoint

**19.1 Purpose.** This Section collapses each mutable external reference in this License into a bounded set of Canonical References, all resolved at a single public resource. The effect is that operational changes to the Licensor's publishing surface, artefact composition, contact address, legal name, marks, and published claims do not require a new version of this License.

**19.2 Master Resolver Endpoint.** The Master Resolver Endpoint is the URL identified at the head of this License, or such successor URL as the Licensor publishes under Section 19.5. At the Master Resolver Endpoint the Licensor publishes, and maintains current, the Canonical References defined in Section 19.3.

**19.3 Canonical References.** The following references are the Canonical References for this License:

(a) **Artefact Bundle Register** — the current composition of each Covered Artefact's Artefact Bundle and the Canonical Bundle Hashes of each constituent file (one Register per Covered Artefact, or a single combined Register that distinguishes Covered Artefacts unambiguously);

(b) **Claims Document (per Covered Artefact)** — the current statement of what each Covered Artefact is claimed to be, to do, and to produce;

(c) **Is/Is-Not Document (per Covered Artefact)** — the current statement of what each Covered Artefact is not claimed to be, to do, or to produce;

(d) **Retractions Register (per Covered Artefact)** — the current record of retractions, including without limitation prior-published claims so recorded;

(e) **Licensor Contact** — the current address for notices under Section 11, Commercial Licensing Intake under Section 14, and dispute notices under Section 17;

(f) **Licensor Identity** — the Licensor's current legal name and domicile, where different from that stated in the header of this License;

(g) **Trademark Register** — the current list of the Licensor's marks relevant to the Licensed Work, including without limitation "Zer0pa," "DM3," and "Genesis";

(h) **License Date For This Version** — the date on which this License version was first published at the Master Resolver Endpoint;

(i) **Supplemental Novelty or Construction Schedules** — any Licensor-published schedule further describing the construction, adjacency, or tags of the DM3 geometry or the Genesis substrate, expressly stated to be incorporated into this License for the purpose of artefact identification. None are in force as at the License Date.

**19.4 Updates Are Not Amendments.** An update to any Canonical Reference published at the Master Resolver Endpoint is operational in nature and does not constitute an amendment of this License. Counterparties rely on the Canonical Reference as in force at the time of the act in question; prior versions of a Canonical Reference remain available in the Endpoint's history for evidentiary purposes.

**19.5 Relocation.** The Licensor may relocate the Master Resolver Endpoint to a successor URL by (a) publishing, at the current Master Resolver Endpoint, a relocation notice identifying the successor URL, and (b) maintaining the relocation notice at the current Endpoint for at least ninety (90) days. On and after the ninety-day mark, the successor URL is the Master Resolver Endpoint.

**19.5.1 Emergency Relocation.** Where the Licensor loses the ability to publish at the current Master Resolver Endpoint (including by reason of platform unavailability, account suspension, or takedown), the Licensor may relocate by publishing the relocation notice at a Licensor-controlled fallback surface (including a `zer0pa.ai` path or sub-domain). The ninety-day period begins from publication at the fallback surface. The Licensor will take commercially reasonable steps to make the relocation notice discoverable.

**19.6 Counterparty Reliance.** A counterparty acting in good-faith reliance on a Canonical Reference at the time of the act is not in breach of this License by reason of a subsequent update to that Canonical Reference, provided the counterparty comes into compliance with the updated Canonical Reference prospectively.

**19.7 Substantive Terms Unchanged.** Nothing in this Section 19 permits the Licensor to alter the substantive terms of this License — the grant (Section 4), the Restrictions (Section 6), the Receipt Chain and Retraction terms (Section 7), the Traditional Knowledge Acknowledgment (Section 8), the Change Date mechanics (Section 10), the Revenue Threshold amount (Section 5), the Hosted Service restriction (Section 6.1), the governing law (Section 17.1), or any other text of this License other than the Canonical References — without publishing a new version of this License.

**19.8 Construction.** Where this License refers to a Canonical Reference, the reference is to the Canonical Reference as in force at the Master Resolver Endpoint at the time of the act in question, except where this License expressly refers to the Canonical Reference "as at the License Date" or similar.

